
Overview of verb hope

The verb hope has 3 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (60) hope, trust, desire -- (expect and wish; "I trust you will behave better from now on"; "I hope she understands that she cannot expect a raise")
2. (37) hope -- (be optimistic; be full of hope; have hopes; "I am still hoping that all will turn out well")
3. (23) hope, go for -- (intend with some possibility of fulfilment; "I hope to have finished this work by tomorrow evening")
